column1: # No specific location given on the sheets - Dalton Holme is the name of the parish rather than a specific property.
# The grid reference on the 1950s sheet and the church directions put the gauge in South Dalton near The Mount.
# The elevation of 120 ft used on the later sheets is a better match (but still a bit high) for this location than the earlier figure of 150ft.
# The station is still active according to MIDAS.
